                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-08T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1920—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received February 8—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Referring to the Legation’s telegram of January 19, 8 p.m.<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d615fn83">Probably refers to Legation’s undated telegram, <ref
                            target="#pg_621">p. 621</ref>.</note> Four Ministers offered 5,000,000
                    pound sterling loan on three conditions specified. Chinese Government has
                    replied accepting conditions and asking immediate advance of 7,000,000 dollars
                    pending completion of negotiations for large loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
